title: High-level government delegation to visit Singapore
content_text: A senior government delegation, led by Secretary for Health and Welfare, Dr E K Yeoh, will visit Singapore from May 23 to 26 to exchange views and experiences on the future development of health and welfare services in the two cities. The visit is organized by the Singapore Ministry of Community Development and Sports. Members of the delegation include Mr Robin Gill, Deputy Secretary for Health and Welfare; Mrs Patricia Chu, Deputy Director of Social Welfare; and Mrs Tang Lai Yuen-yee, Chief Social Work Officer (Service Performance Section) of the Social Welfare Department.
